President Obama will be visiting Detroit on September 5th to celebrate Labor Day with workers and their families. He will also discuss his efforts to create jobs and strengthen the economy. Secretary of Labor Hilda L. Solis will accompany him on the trip. The arrival and departure of Air Force One at Detroit Metro Wayne County Airport will be open to pre-credentialed media members but closed to the public. The event in Detroit will be open to pre-credentialed media members and the public. Before the event, there will be musical performances by the Mosaic Youth Theater of Detroit and Aretha Franklin.